{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"300112","heading":"Office of the Ombudsman","label":"300112 Office of the Ombudsman","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s300112","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/stIII/ch3001","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs300112","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Establishment","label":"a .—Establishment","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s300112/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s300112","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs300112%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The corporation shall establish an Office of the Ombudsman with such duties and responsibilities as may be provided in the bylaws or a resolution of the board of governors.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Report.—","label":"b Report.—","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s300112/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s300112","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs300112%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":".—In general","label":"1 .—In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s300112/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t36/s300112/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft36%2Fs300112%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Office of the Ombudsman shall submit annually to the appropriate Congressional committees a report concerning any trends and systemic matters that the Office of the Ombudsman has identified as confronting the corporation.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":".—Appropriate c